      • create

        public static WorldConfiguration create(java.lang.String name,
                                        DimensionType dimensionType)
        Creates a new WorldConfig for use with WorldManager.createWorld(WorldConfiguration)

        Before passing on to createWorld, these settings should be modified using getFile()
        and then calling net.visualillusionsent.utils.PropertiesFile#save() followed with reload() when finished

        • worldType (String)
        • spawn-protection (Integer)
        • max-build-height (Integer)
        • generate-structures (Boolean)
        • generator-settings (String)
        • world-seed (String)
        • startup-autoload (Boolean)
        • warp-autoload (Boolean)
        • allow-nether (Boolean)
        • allow-end (Boolean)
        • allow-flight (Boolean)
        • pvp (Boolean)
        • difficulty (Integer)
        • gamemode (Integer)
        • forceDefaultGameMode (Boolean)
        • forceDefaultGameModeDimensional (Boolean)
        • auto-heal (String)
        • enable-experience (Boolean)
        • enable-health (Boolean)
        • spawn-villagers (Boolean)
        • spawn-golems (Boolean)
        • spawn-animals (Boolean)
        • spawn-monsters (Boolean)
        • natural-animals (String[])
        • natural-monsters (String[])
        • natural-golems (String[])
        • natural-wateranimals (String[])
        • natural-spawn-rate (Integer)
        • ender-blocks (int[])
        • disallowed-blocks (int[])

        NOTE: Settings list may not be entirely up to date.
        Parameters:
        name - name of the World
        dimensionType - DimensionType of the world
        Returns:
        the new WorldConfiguraion or null if a configuration is already existant
        See Also:
        WorldManager.createWorld(WorldConfiguration), reload(), getFile()
